{{otheruses|Shinobu Sanzan Akatsuki Mairi, a Shinto ritual held in February during the lunar New Year|Fukushima Waraji Festival, a summer event held in August|福島わらじまつり}}
'''Shinobu Sanzan Akatsuki Mairi''' (信夫三山暁まいり) is a {{ill|Shinto ritual|ja|神事|12=draft|12=draft}} held annually from {{ill|February 10|ja|2月10日|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|February 11|ja|2月11日|12=draft|12=draft}}, coinciding with the 14th day of the lunar New Year. It takes place on {{ill|Mount Shinobu|ja|信夫山|12=draft|12=draft}}, located in the center of {{ill|Fukushima City|ja|福島市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|12=draft|12=draft}}.
{{seealso|Fukushima Waraji Festival}}
== Overview == Mount Shinobu, adjacent to the urban area of Fukushima City, is venerated through {{ill|mountain worship|ja|山岳信仰|12=draft|12=draft}} that honors its three peaks: Hayama, Haguroyama, and Kumano-yama. This festival boasts nearly 400 years of history and is recognized as one of Fukushima Prefecture’s most representative events, distinguished by the offering of Japan’s largest straw sandal (*waraji*). The sandal bearers include local volunteers from the Oyama Keishinkai and members of the local chamber of commerce, with local elementary school students participating as bearers of the children’s *waraji*.
The main route starts in the Oyama district on the northern peak of Mount Shinobu, proceeds counterclockwise through the area near {{ill|Fukushima Station|ja|福島駅|12=draft|12=draft}} East Exit, traverses the city center, and enters Mount Shinobu from the southern peak, culminating with an offering at {{ill|Haguro Shrine|ja|羽黒神社|12=draft|12=draft}} at the summit.
In terms of media coverage, the event is broadcast live annually by the local {{ill|community radio|ja|コミュニティ放送|12=draft|12=draft}} station {{ill|FM Poco|ja|福島コミュニティ放送|12=draft|12=draft}}, available for free nationwide via online streaming.
A massive *waraji* measuring 12 meters in length, 1.2 meters in width, and weighing approximately 2 tons is carried during the event.
== Giant Waraji Procession Route == * Oyama Workshop (along {{ill|National Route 13 (Japan)|ja|国道13号|12=draft|12=draft}}) * {{ill|Sato Construction Headquarters|ja|佐藤工業 (福島市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (along {{ill|Fukushima Iizaka Line|ja|福島県道3号福島飯坂線|12=draft|12=draft}}) * {{ill|Fukushima Naritasan Fudoin|ja|福島成田山不動院|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Soneda Station|ja|曽根田駅|12=draft|12=draft}} / {{ill|MAX Fukushima|ja|曽根田ショッピングセンター|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Fukushima Station|ja|福島駅|12=draft|12=draft}} East Exit * Fukushima Financial District (Brick Street) * {{ill|Fukushima Inari Shrine|ja|福島稲荷神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (former guardian shrine of the Fukushima Castle town area) * Paseo Street Shopping District * Fukushima Fire Department * Entry to Mount Shinobu * {{ill|Kurōnuma Shrine|ja|黒沼神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (guardian shrine of the former {{ill|Koyama Arai Village|ja|小山荒井村|12=draft|12=draft}} area) * {{ill|Fukushima Gokoku Shrine|ja|福島縣護國神社|12=draft|12=draft}} * Mount Shinobu Guide Center * {{ill|Haguro Shrine|ja|羽黒神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (summit)
== Events == On the 10th, the "Akatsuki Mairi Fukuotoko Fukujyo Race" (*暁まいり福男福女競走*) is held, with participants competing along a route similar to the *waraji* procession.
== Access == On the day of the event, temporary free parking lots are set up at various locations around the southern peak of Mount Shinobu.
== External Links == * [Official Website of the Shinobu Sanzan Akatsuki Mairi (if available)]
* [http://www.f-kankou.jp/cgi-bin/f-kankou/asobu/page.cgi?id=70 信夫三山暁まいり] - 福島市観光コンベンション協会 * [https://www.ntt-east.co.jp/fukushima/fbrari/031/05.html イベント「信夫三山暁まいり」] - NTT東日本福島支店
